<task id="AIPU2-088" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build ProgressTrackerWidget for Context Pane</title>
    <phase>4D</phase>
    <tags>frontend, widgets, progress</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-073</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Multi-step AI operations (e.g., contract review pipelines, due diligence workflows) run
    multiple playbook steps sequentially. Users have no visibility into which step is running
    and how far through the workflow they are. ProgressTrackerWidget renders workflow step
    progress in the Context pane during the progress stage. It receives step updates via
    context_update PaneEventBus events and renders a vertical step list: completed steps
    (checkmark), the active step (spinner), and pending steps (circle). It is intentionally
    simple — no estimated time, no cancellation — to avoid complexity while providing essential
    progress visibility.
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with React 19 and Fluent v9 experience.</role>
  <goal>
    Workflow step progress renders in the Context pane with completed/active/pending step states.
    Step states update via PaneEventBus events. Widget registered in ContextWidgetRegistry.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read ADR-021 for Fluent v9 icon and token guidance (Checkmark, ProgressBar, Circle icons from @fluentui/react-icons).</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/ProgressTrackerWidget.tsx implementing ContextWidget.</step>
    <step>Define ProgressTrackerData type: { steps: WorkflowStep[] } where WorkflowStep has id, label, status ('completed' | 'active' | 'pending'), and optional substepLabel.</step>
    <step>Render a vertical list of steps using Fluent v9 layout: completed steps show a CheckmarkCircle icon (colorPaletteGreenForeground1 token), active step shows a Spinner, pending steps show an empty Circle icon in muted token color.</step>
    <step>Subscribe to additional context_update events on the 'context' channel within the widget — when a new progress event arrives, replace the step list state reactively (no cumulative merging, the server sends full state each time).</step>
    <step>Handle edge cases: empty step list renders a Fluent v9 Spinner only; all steps completed transitions the stage (dispatch context_update to 'related-items' stage via PaneEventBus after a brief delay).</step>
    <step>Register ProgressTrackerWidget in ContextWidgetRegistry.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: completed/active/pending steps render correct icons and colors; context_update replaces step list; all-completed triggers stage transition dispatch.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Completed steps show CheckmarkCircle icon with green Fluent token; active step shows Spinner; pending steps show muted Circle icon.</criterion>
    <criterion>Step list replaces fully on each context_update event (server sends full state).</criterion>
    <criterion>All-completed state dispatches a context_update to 'related-items' stage on PaneEventBus.</criterion>
    <criterion>Empty step list renders a Spinner only — not a blank pane.</criterion>
    <criterion>Widget registered in ContextWidgetRegistry and renders during progress stage.</criterion>
    <criterion>No hard-coded colors — Fluent v9 tokens only (ADR-021).</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests for step icon states, replacement, and all-completed transition pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
